                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16659697" author="thw" created="Mon, 22 Oct 2018 21:27:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Underlying (larger) issue is that DoFnOperator.dispose can trigger new bundles (yikes!). That&apos;s not what one would expect, especially not after a job was cancelled.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16660270" author="mxm" created="Tue, 23 Oct 2018 08:35:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=thw&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;thw&quot;&gt;thw&lt;/a&gt; Didn&apos;t we already move the shutdown of the SDK harness client to the dipose method? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16660769" author="thw" created="Tue, 23 Oct 2018 14:52:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I changed the title to reflect the issue that needs to be looked into. We are working around it in the portable runner by assuming that the dispose call can fail because of the unexpected bundle processing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
